{"tiddlers":{"$:/vocab/fountain/styles":{"title":"$:/vocab/fountain/styles","created":"20260519092959557","modified":"20260519161500000","tags":"$:/tags/Stylesheet","type":"text/vnd.tiddlywiki","text":"\rules only filteredtranscludeinline transcludeinline macrodef macrocallinline html

/* ---- Typography baseline -----------------------------------------
   Monospace face for the typewriter feel of a shooting script. Applied
   per class because there's no wrapping container; a future engine
   change could inject one, in which case font-family would move there.
   max-width:60ch on each block approximates the printed-page width
   (~60 columns of Courier on a US Letter page with 1" margins).
*/

.wltc-fountain-scene-heading,
.wltc-fountain-transition,
.wltc-fountain-fade-in,
.wltc-fountain-character,
.wltc-fountain-action,
.wltc-fountain-synopsis,
.wltc-fountain-section,
.wltc-front-matter,
.wltc-fountain-centered {
	font-family: "Courier New", Courier, monospace;
	font-size: 1em;
	line-height: 1.3;
}

/* ---- Title page (front-matter) -----------------------------------
   Centered key:value block at the top of the tiddler. The on-page
   convention shows values only (the `Title:` / `Author:` keys are
   visual scaffolding, not content), so the key span is hidden.
   First row is enlarged as a stand-in for the screenplay title.
*/

.wltc-front-matter {
	text-align: center;
	margin: 3em auto 4em;
	padding: 2em 0;
	max-width: 60ch;
	border-bottom: 1px dotted #ddd;
}

.wltc-front-matter-key {
	display: none;
}

.wltc-front-matter-row {
	margin: 0.5em 0;
}

.wltc-front-matter-row:first-child {
	font-size: 1.4em;
	font-weight: bold;
	margin: 1em 0 2em;
}

.wltc-front-matter-row[data-key="Source"] {
	font-style: italic;
	margin-bottom: 2em;
}

.wltc-front-matter-row[data-key="Copyright"] {
	margin-top: 3em;
	font-size: 0.85em;
	color: #666;
}

/* ---- Scene headings ----------------------------------------------
   Industry convention: at the left margin, bold uppercase. Slightly
   more top spacing than a paragraph break to separate scenes.
*/

.wltc-fountain-scene-heading {
	text-transform: uppercase;
	font-weight: bold;
	margin-top: 2em;
	margin-bottom: 0.5em;
}

/* ---- Action paragraphs -------------------------------------------
   Left margin, regular case, narrow screenplay-page width.
*/

.wltc-fountain-action {
	margin: 1em 0;
	max-width: 60ch;
}

/* ---- Character cue + dialogue ------------------------------------
   Cue is centered uppercase in a narrow column. Dialogue follows on
   the next paragraph(s); we can only reliably target the immediately
   adjacent <p> with CSS — multi-paragraph dialogue runs need engine
   support for lookahead (bd-j5b).
*/

.wltc-fountain-character {
	text-transform: uppercase;
	text-align: center;
	margin: 1.2em auto 0;
	max-width: 20ch;
}

.wltc-fountain-character + p {
	margin: 0 auto 1em;
	max-width: 35ch;
	font-family: "Courier New", Courier, monospace;
}

/* ---- Transitions -------------------------------------------------
   Mid-script transitions sit at the right margin; the FADE IN opener
   stays at left per the spec.
*/

.wltc-fountain-transition {
	text-transform: uppercase;
	text-align: right;
	margin: 1em 0;
	max-width: 60ch;
}

.wltc-fountain-fade-in {
	text-transform: uppercase;
	text-align: left;
	margin: 1em 0;
	max-width: 60ch;
}

/* ---- Synopsis ----------------------------------------------------
   Author-only note. Light italic gray so it's distinguishable from
   produced action.
*/

.wltc-fountain-synopsis {
	font-style: italic;
	color: #888;
	margin-left: 2em;
	margin-top: 0.5em;
	margin-bottom: 0.5em;
	font-size: 0.95em;
}

/* ---- Boneyard ----------------------------------------------------
   Author-side cuts; hidden from rendered output.
*/

.wltc-fountain-boneyard {
	display: none;
}

/* ---- Sections (author outline headers) ---------------------------
   Hierarchical via the standard wltc-l<N> level classes.
*/

.wltc-fountain-section {
	font-weight: bold;
	text-transform: uppercase;
	color: #555;
	margin-top: 2em;
	margin-bottom: 0.5em;
	border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
	padding-bottom: 0.2em;
	max-width: 60ch;
}

.wltc-fountain-section.wltc-l1 { font-size: 1.2em; }
.wltc-fountain-section.wltc-l2 { font-size: 1.05em; margin-left: 1em; }
.wltc-fountain-section.wltc-l3 { font-size: 1em; margin-left: 2em; }
.wltc-fountain-section.wltc-l4 { font-size: 0.95em; margin-left: 3em; }

/* ---- Centered text ----------------------------------------------- */

.wltc-fountain-centered {
	display: block;
	text-align: center;
	margin: 1em 0;
}

/* ---- Inline emphasis --------------------------------------------- */

.wltc-fountain-bold-italic {
	font-style: italic;
}

.wltc-fountain-underline {
	text-decoration: underline;
}
"},"$:/plugins/wikilabs/custom-markup/ui/ControlPanel/CustomMarkup":{"title":"$:/plugins/wikilabs/custom-markup/ui/ControlPanel/CustomMarkup","tags":"$:/tags/ControlPanel/Advanced","caption":"Custom Markup","text":"\whitespace trim

<p>{{$:/plugins/wikilabs/custom-markup!!description}}</p>

<p>CM Plugin Version: <code>{{$:/plugins/wikilabs/custom-markup!!version}}</code>. <$link to="$:/plugins/wikilabs/custom-markup" class="tc-tiny-gap-left">Plugin tiddler</$link> &middot; <$link to="$:/plugins/wikilabs/custom-markup/readme"  class="tc-tiny-gap-left">Readme</$link> &middot; <$link to="$:/plugins/wikilabs/custom-markup/history"  class="tc-tiny-gap-left">History</$link></p>

!! Vocabularies

Each vocab ships a set of markers. Activate per tiddler via the type field (<code>;vocab=Name</code>) or via <code>\importcustom</code>. Click a caption to open the vocab summary (full marker table and "Used in" list).

<table class="tc-table-no-border">
<thead>
<tr><th>Caption</th><th align="right">Markers</th><th>Marker tag</th><th>Activate via type</th></tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<$list filter="[all[shadows+tiddlers]tag[$:/tags/CustomMarkup/Vocabulary]sort[caption]]">
<tr>
<td><$link to=<<currentTiddler>>>{{!!caption}}</$link></td>
<td align="right">{{{ [all[shadows+tiddlers]tag<currentTiddler>tag[$:/tags/CustomMarkup/Marker]count[]] }}}</td>
<td><code><$text text=<<currentTiddler>>/></code></td>
<td><code>;vocab={{!!caption}}</code></td>
</tr>
</$list>
</tbody>
</table>

<p>Vocabulary tag: <$link to="$:/tags/CustomMarkup/Vocabulary"><code>$:/tags/CustomMarkup/Vocabulary</code></$link></p>

!! Markers

<$let
	total={{{ [all[shadows+tiddlers]tag[$:/tags/CustomMarkup/Marker]count[]] }}}
	glyph={{{ [all[shadows+tiddlers]tag[$:/tags/CustomMarkup/Marker]field:kind[glyph]count[]] }}}
	glyphLevel={{{ [all[shadows+tiddlers]tag[$:/tags/CustomMarkup/Marker]field:kind[glyph-level]count[]] }}}
	word={{{ [all[shadows+tiddlers]tag[$:/tags/CustomMarkup/Marker]field:kind[word]count[]] }}}
	inlinePair={{{ [all[shadows+tiddlers]tag[$:/tags/CustomMarkup/Marker]field:kind[inline-pair]count[]] }}}
	listItem={{{ [all[shadows+tiddlers]tag[$:/tags/CustomMarkup/Marker]field:kind[list-item]count[]] }}}
>
<table class="tc-table-no-border">
<thead><tr><th>Kind</th><th align="right">Count</th></tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td>''Total''</td><td align="right">''<<total>>''</td></tr>
<tr><td><code>glyph</code></td><td align="right"><<glyph>></td></tr>
<tr><td><code>glyph-level</code></td><td align="right"><<glyphLevel>></td></tr>
<tr><td><code>word</code></td><td align="right"><<word>></td></tr>
<tr><td><code>inline-pair</code></td><td align="right"><<inlinePair>></td></tr>
<tr><td><code>list-item</code></td><td align="right"><<listItem>></td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</$let>

<p>Marker tag: <$link to="$:/tags/CustomMarkup/Marker"><code>$:/tags/CustomMarkup/Marker</code></$link></p>

!! Global pragmas

Tiddlers tagged <code>$:/tags/Pragma</code> are bridged into every parser at init time via the page template's <code>\importcustom</code>. Use these for legacy <code>\custom &lt;kind&gt;=&lt;symbol&gt;</code> definitions that should apply wiki-wide.

<ul>
<$list filter="[all[shadows+tiddlers]tag[$:/tags/Pragma]sort[title]]" emptyMessage="(none)">
<li><$link/></li>
</$list>
</ul>

<p>Page-template container: <$link to="$:/config/custom-markup/pragma/PageTemplate"><code>$:/config/custom-markup/pragma/PageTemplate</code></$link></p>

!! Debug pragmas

* <code>\debugcustom</code>. Parse-time registry inspector. Forms: <code>\debugcustom</code>, <code>\debugcustom list</code>, <code>\debugcustom &lt;open-or-legacy-kind&gt;</code>, <code>\debugcustom global ...</code>, <code>\debugcustom no</code>.

* <code>\debugmarker</code>. Per-tiddler render-time mode override for a marker's <code>debug</code> field. Forms: <code>\debugmarker &lt;open&gt;=&lt;mode&gt;</code>, <code>\debugmarker &lt;open&gt;=no</code>, <code>\debugmarker no</code>. Modes: <code>pragma</code>, <code>pragmaOnly</code>, <code>text</code>, <code>textOnly</code>, <code>both</code>, <code>no</code>.

!! Editor toolbar

Buttons and dropdowns the plugin contributes to the text-editor toolbar.

<ul class="multi-columns">
<$list filter="[all[shadows+tiddlers]tag[$:/tags/EditorToolbar]prefix[$:/plugins/wikilabs/custom-markup/]sort[title]]" emptyMessage="<li>(none)</li>">
<li><$link/></li>
</$list>
</ul>

!! Templates and cascades

View-template body cascades installed by the plugin (route marker / marker-tag / vocab tiddlers to their dedicated summary views).

<ul class="multi-columns">
<$list filter="[all[shadows+tiddlers]tag[$:/tags/ViewTemplateBodyFilter]prefix[$:/plugins/wikilabs/custom-markup/]sort[title]]" emptyMessage="(none)">
<li><$link/></li>
</$list>
</ul>

Summary-view templates:

<ul class="multi-columns">
<$list filter="[all[shadows+tiddlers]prefix[$:/plugins/wikilabs/custom-markup/ViewTemplate/body/]sort[title]]" emptyMessage="(none)">
<li><$link/></li>
</$list>
</ul>
