"},"$:/plugins/wikilabs/custom-markup/history":{"title":"$:/plugins/wikilabs/custom-markup/history","text":"V 1.0.0-beta-35 - 2026-05-23

* V 1.0.0-beta-35
** Vocabulary meta tiddlers no longer need a `marker-tag` field. The vocabulary's title is automatically the tag its markers carry — one less field to author and keep in sync.

V 1.0.0-beta-34 - 2026-05-21

* V 1.0.0-beta-34
** `debug` and `debug-string` fields on marker tiddlers: per-marker render-time codeblock. Modes `pragma`, `pragmaOnly`, `text`, `textOnly`, `both`, `no`.
** `\debugmarker <open>=<mode>` pragma: per-tiddler override of a marker's `debug` field.
** ControlPanel > Advanced > "Custom Markup": navigation dashboard for vocabularies, markers, global pragmas, toolbar and cascades.

V 1.0.0-beta-33 - 2026-05-20

* V 1.0.0-beta-33
** Fix: global pragmas (`°clip`, `°sc`, etc. from `$:/tags/Pragma` tiddlers) no longer fall through to the marker default. Activation was replacing the marker config and dropping the `globalSymbols` bindings attached by `loadGlobalPragmas`.

* V 1.0.0-beta-32
** New marker kind `list-item`: consecutive items collapse into a `container` element (ul/ol/dl/blockquote), nesting via indent. New fields: `container`, `item-element`, `indent-unit`, `open-pattern`. Markdown's list bullets now ship as marker tiddlers; `markdown-list.js` removed.
** View templates list fields dynamically created

* V 1.0.0-beta-31
** New `markdown-newline` inline wikirule: any intra-paragraph `\n` emits `<br>`.
** New `markdown-table` block wikirule: pipe tables with separator row and alignment colons; cell content parses as an inline run.

* V 1.0.0-beta-30
** Inline-pair `body-raw: yes`: body is captured as a single literal text node, no recursive parsing. Enables code-span markers that preserve raw HTML and wikitext.
** New `markdown-list` block wikirule (gated on the markdown vocab): `-`/`*`/`+` for `<ul>`, `<digits>.` for `<ol>`, 2-space indent per nesting level.
** `CmRegistry.activeVocabs` + `isActiveVocab(title)`: lets wikirules gate on a specific vocab being active for the current parser.
** Override the internals raw-preview template to use `$wikify` with `type={{!!type}}` so parametric types (`;vocab=...`) preview correctly.
** `wltc-l<n>` class is now only emitted for `glyph-level` markers.

* V 1.0.0-beta-29
** Vocab activation resolves `;vocab=Name` by direct `getTiddler("vocab/" + name.toLowerCase())` instead of a `field:caption` filter walk over all shadow+tiddlers. Around 33x faster microbench (3.46 to 0.10 µs/op for one vocab; 6.80 to 0.18 µs/op for the typical two-vocab activation). Convention: vocab title must be `vocab/<lowercase-caption>`.

V 1.0.0-beta-28 - 2026-05-19

* V 1.0.0-beta-28
** Inactive marker positions no longer shadow TW core rules. `cmblock` and `cminline` now override `findNextMatch` to skip matches whose marker isn't active in the current tiddler (gated by a `_cmPragmasDone` flag so pragma-activated vocabs still work). Previously a marker with a common open like `#` or `*` would eat the position via text-fallback in `parse()`, suppressing the competing core rule (e.g. TW ordered lists) for every tiddler in the wiki — even ones that didn't activate the offending vocab.
** `\importcustom <filter>` now runs the filter over `[all[shadows+tiddlers]]` automatically, so `\importcustom [tag[Vocab/X]]` finds shadow markers without the author having to spell the shadow-inclusion prefix. Type-field activation already had this behaviour.
** Vocab-summary ViewTemplate splits "Mode" / "Element" columns from new "Default Mode" / "Default Element" columns so the kind-implied defaults stay visible alongside any explicit overrides.

* V 1.0.0-beta-27
** Inline-pair arms sort longest-open-first so multi-char markers like `***` win over `**` and `*` at the same position.
** Inline-pair markers honor `allow-symbol: no` (previously only block-glyph markers did); required for body-only markers like Fountain's `*italic*`.
** `emit-open: yes` prepends a trailing space when the body is non-empty so the open literal and body don't run together (`INT. KITCHEN`, not `INT.KITCHEN`).
** New `frontmatter` wikirule: when an active vocab declares `front-matter: yes`, a YAML block at the very top of the tiddler is consumed and rendered as `<div class="wltc-front-matter">`. Terminated by blank line or `===`. Parsing uses a vendored copy of the minimal YAML library from Jermolene's TiddlyWiki5 PR #9806 (`bidirectional-filesystem` branch).

* V 1.0.0-beta-26
** Vocab meta `disable-core-rules: <names>` suppresses listed TW core wikirules for tiddlers that activate the vocab; user `\rules` pragmas can still amend further.
** Marker field `emit-open: yes` prepends the marker's open literal to its rendered body (for word markers where the keyword IS the content).

* V 1.0.0-beta-25
** Cross-vocab marker collisions (two vocabs with the same `open`) now resolve to the LAST activated vocab. Type field `;vocab=A,B` makes B win on overlap; `;vocab=B,A` makes A win. Previously the alphabetically-last marker tiddler always won regardless of activation.

* V 1.0.0-beta-24
** Drop redundant `(function(){ ... })()` wrappers from 7 JS modules. TW's module loader already encapsulates.

* V 1.0.0-beta-23
** Secure-by-default: iframe markers get `sandbox=""` injected (max restrictions; neutralizes srcdoc-script and external-content vectors). `object`/`embed`/`frame`/`frameset` are denied (no usable sandbox). `javascript:` URLs are stripped from `src`/`href`/`xlink:href`/`data`/`action`/`formaction`. Opt out per marker with `allow-unsafe: yes` (or pragma `_allow_unsafe=yes`).

* V 1.0.0-beta-22
** `\custom <kind>=<sym> _activate=no` opts out of the implicit marker activation. Useful for pragmas that only exist to be referenced via `_useGlobal` from other tiddlers.

* V 1.0.0-beta-21
** Plugin-side `$:/config/custom-markup/pragma/PageTemplate` corrected: tag `$:/tags/Macro`

* V 1.0.0-beta-20
** ViewTemplate body cascade split: one tiddler per clause.
** Marker-summary: open/close glyphs in a two-column table.

* V 1.0.0-beta-19
** Vocab-summary table adds `Max-level` and `Paragraph` columns; marker-summary view adds a `paragraph-marker` row.

* V 1.0.0-beta-18
** `paragraph-marker: yes` field on marker tiddlers opts into paragraph terminator semantics (blank-line, no nested-p body parse). Shipped paragraph markers (ANGLE, APPROX, PILCROW) declare it explicitly.

V 1.0.0-beta-16 - 2026-05-18

* V 1.0.0-beta-16
** Dropped orphan ShortcutInfo entries for add-angle, remove-angle, toggle-tick.

* V 1.0.0-beta-15
** Removed legacy hardcoded-glyph buttons add-tick, remove-tick, toggle-tick, add-angle, remove-angle. Use the vocab dropdowns instead.


* V 1.0.0-beta-14
** `\debugcustom` lists v1 markers as well as legacy kinds; lookup by `open` literal works.
** Editor toolbar add/remove/toggle glyph and toggle-inline buttons show on `;vocab=...` types.

* V 1.0.0-beta-13

** Toolbar prefix and inline dropdowns are `<select>` widgets; Vocab/Default ordered Angle, Single, Dot, Degree.
** `$:/vocab/*` tiddlers show a summary view.

* V 1.0.0-beta-12

** Editor toolbar add/remove glyph buttons enabled only for markers with `max-level > 1` (ANGLE, SINGLE, APPROX, PILCROW); toggle enabled for any line-prefix marker. Filter reads the marker tiddler directly.

* V 1.0.0-beta-11

** Internal: use TW core's `parseTiddler` for the global-pragma cache. No behaviour change.

* V 1.0.0-beta-10

** PageTemplate global pragmas are cached per wiki; ~3× faster wikitext parse on tiddlers with custom markup.

* V 1.0.0-beta-9

** `marker-icon` field on each marker tiddler; new `dot` icon.
** Marker tiddler and `$:/tags/CustomMarkup/Marker` tag show summary views.
** Edit-view type input widens for `;vocab=...` types.

------

V 1.0.0-beta-8 - 2026-05-17

* V 1.0.0-beta-8

** `\custom <kind>=<sym> _mode=block` on non-paragraph markers (`´`, `°`, `›`) now defaults to single-newline body termination. Tables built with `´td`-per-line work again.

* V 1.0.0-beta-7

** `\custom <kind>=<sym> ...` now auto-activates the marker for the tiddler — author defining custom behaviour implies the marker should fire.
** `_endString="\n"` (and `\r`, `\t`, `\\`, `\"`, `\'`) finally interprets the JS escapes instead of matching the literal `\n` characters.
** `_useGlobal=<sym>` switches to the global target wholesale; only local `_debug` wins, so the debug codeblock shows the resolved config.
** Trailing newline no longer leaks into widget `src` attribute or debug `text` codeblock when the terminator is eaten.

* V 1.0.0-beta-6

** `_use` and `_useGlobal` pragma aliases follow through to the target.
** `_debug=pragma|text|both|*Only|no` emits the pragma string and/or source slice as a code block.
** `°` `›` default to single-newline body termination again; `»` `≈` `¶` to blank-line.

* V 1.0.0-beta-5

** `:"<arg>"` positional arguments after the symbol/class chain now feed `_params` widget attributes (`°☐:"a"` overrides the first `_params` entry from the bridged pragma).
** Indirect / macro / filtered attribute values (`field={{!!yy}}`, `UID=<<qualify>>`) survive into the registry; previously stringified to `[object Object]`.
** Global `\custom` pragmas from `$:/config/custom-markup/pragma/PageTemplate` are loaded into every parser, restoring wiki-wide marker shortcuts (e.g. `°clip`, `°example`).
** `»` `≈` `¶` markers wrap as `<p class="...">...</p>` again instead of `<div><p>...</p></div>`, matching the v0.x rendering.
** Widget `src` no longer carries a trailing newline (which became `%0A` in URL-valued attributes).

------

V 1.0.0-beta-4 - 2026-05-16

* V 1.0.0-beta-4

** `\custom <unknown-kind>` (anything outside the 9 legacy kinds) no longer crashes the parse rule.

* V 1.0.0-beta-3

** Bare-kind pragmas (`\custom angle _element=td`) now activate the marker's default override.
** Block-position fires always wrap in a block element; `wltc-l<N>` level class always added.

* V 1.0.0-beta-2

** Editor toolbar dropdowns filter by the active vocabulary for the tiddler being edited (vocabs come from the `;vocab=` parameter on the type field; defaults to Vocab/Default).
** New `cm-active-markers` filter operator: `[<tiddler>cm-active-markers[block|inline|word]]` returns marker titles active for that tiddler.
** Inline-pair dropdown lists `/° °/` first (SLASH gets `order: 1`; sort chain `sort[caption]!sort[order]`).

* V 1.0.0-beta-1 (Breaking changes)

** Markers are now tiddlers tagged `$:/tags/CustomMarkup/Marker`, grouped into vocabularies (`Vocab/<Name>`). Default vocabulary ships `°` `.` `»` `›` (block) and `/° °/`, `❮ ❯`, `⠒ ⠶` (inline-pair). Activate extra vocabularies per tiddler via `type=text/vnd.tiddlywiki;vocab=Default,Legacy-Glyphs` or via `\importcustom [tag[Vocab/X]]`.
** `´` `≈` `¶` moved to opt-in `Vocab/Legacy-Glyphs`. To keep using them, add `;vocab=Default,Legacy-Glyphs` to the tiddler's type field.
** `°` and `›` now default to blank-line termination (was single-newline). Back-to-back `°foo` `°bar` lines join into one block. Set `mode: inline` on the marker tiddler or use `\custom degree=foo _mode=inline` to restore the old single-newline behaviour.
** Editor toolbar dropdowns iterate marker tiddlers; new vocabularies appear automatically.
** New `word` marker kind enables Fountain-flavoured DSLs. `Vocab/Presentation` (in editions) wraps the Reveal.js plugin: `PRESENTATION` / `CUT TO:` / `ANIMATE TO:` / `FADE IN:` / `FADE OUT.`.
** `\custom <kind>=<symbol>` pragma is preserved as an in-tiddler escape hatch and bridges into the new registry via each marker's `legacy-kind` field.
** Dropped the `pragma-comment` plugin dependency (HTML comments are in TW core).

------

